{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_61","type":"agent_message","text":"The second failure is different: Groovy gets past resource loading, then `ReflectionUtils.checkCanSetAccessible` dereferences a `null` `VM_PLUGIN`. `VMPluginFactory` instantiates its Java-version plugin class reflectively by name and swallows any failure, so in native image that usually means the plugin implementation constructor wasn’t registered for reflection."}}
